Daily Report 
<DATE1>  27 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Domestic Trade Ministry To Close Travel Stores </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Domestic Trade Ministry To Close Travel Stores </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2406162194 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 0207 24 
Jun GMT 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2406162194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rene Diaz Olivera, vice minister of domestic trade, 
stated that effective 1 July, stores that sell articles for 
travel abroad will close down. 
  Diaz explained that this measure was taken in light of the 
current shortage of supplies, which became more acute at the end 
of last year and continues this year. For this reason, stores 
such as El Baluarte, La Internacional, and Lujos, which sell 
shoes, clothing, and other goods for travelers, will close down 
on 1 July. Diaz added that organizations and enterprises with 
an established clientele will receive a letter giving more 
details. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

