<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moncada II 94-1 Exercise Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moncada II 94-1 Exercise Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2506022294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2506022294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Marieta Cabrera from the "Exclusive" program] </F>
  [Text] The Western Army's Moncada II 94-1 exercise 
concluded today as an overall part of the command's operation, 
combat, and political preparation. The exercise sought to 
prepare general staff and command members to handle troops, as 
well as to organize the cooperation of regular forces and 
municipal defense councils in the region defended by the Western 
Army. 
  Moncada II 94-1 was based on a series of complex tactical 
exercises, which included ambushes, airborne landings by the 
enemy, and joint actions by the regular troops and other types 
of forces. Today's activities included a naval maneuver at the 
western base of Cabanas, preceded by maneuvers at the Jejenes 
shooting range with the participation of land and antiaircraft 
artillery and support troops. The exercise proved commanders' 
expertise in the deployment of small units which operate 
independently, their maneuverability, their accuracy, and 
efficient fulfillment of missions. Supported by initiatives, 
troop instruction programs were qualitatively carried out, which 
helped save materials and improve combat techniques. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

