<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electric Plants Maintenance Program Announced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electric Plants Maintenance Program Announced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2406145394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2406145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This weekend, generator unit no. 3 of the Carlos 
Manuel de Cespedes Electric Plant will go on a 35-day 
maintenance program in order to reestablish its full capability 
of 158 megawatts per hour. Electric maintenance and Construction 
Ministry workers have the necessary resources to conduct the 
maintenance with the required quality and complete it ahead of 
schedule. The plant workers are also working to reactivate the 
30 megawatts per hour generator unit no. 1, which has been 
inoperative for three years. Their goal is to make it 
operational as soon as possible. 
  On 27 June, workers will also begin an 80-day repair program 
on the five megawatts per hour unit at the Dionisio San Roman 
plant, Cienfuegos, which has also been out of service. 

</TEXT>

