<F P=100> Dominican Republic </F>
<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Provisional Government Prepares for Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Provisional Government Prepares for Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2406220294 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2406220294 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Jonassaint government is planning elections. 
The provisional government issued a press release following a 
ministerial council meeting on 22 June expressing its 
determination to make all the necessary arrangements for 
national elections as soon as possible and in compliance with 
the concerned institutions. No dates have been set for the 
elections or for the necessary steps to prepare for the 
elections. 
  [Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French at 1030 GMT on 24 
June reports: "Government sources have reported that the 
Jonassaint government will have to summon Permanent Electoral 
Council members next week to discuss national elections. On 17 
June, provisional President Emile Jonassaint said that holding 
elections is the only honorable way out of the crisis and that 
elections will prove democracy can come to Haiti. Attorney 
Mireille Durocher Bertin of the National Coalition agrees and 
has suggested that a team be organized to open the files 
necessary for holding elections in Haiti in the next few 
months."] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

