<H3> <TI>   Ministry Note: Pro-Aristide Acts `Null and Void' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Note: Pro-Aristide Acts `Null and Void' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2406230194 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1500 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2406230194 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Affairs and Cults Ministry has ordered 
former President Jean-Bertrand Aritide and his employees not to 
speak on behalf of the Haitian state or to commit the Republic 
of Haiti to anything with their signatures. This is how it 
appears in the Ministry press release, which adds: The Haitian 
Chancery expresses its most formal reservations over statements 
and actions by members of the overthrown government, statements 
and actions that the Chancery considers null and void. The 
Foreign Affairs and Cults Ministry adds that it has asked the 
OAS secretary general to pass this information on to its various 
members and regional institutions for whatever it's worth. 

</TEXT>

