<H3> <TI>   Jokes About Castro </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jokes About Castro </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2406203394 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1519 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2406203394 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Washington, 24 Jun (NA) -- President Carlos Menem 
today cracked some jokes about his Cuban counterpart Fidel 
Castro. He said Castro "is becoming more modern: He changed his 
combat fatigues for a light shirt [guayabera]" during the recent 
summit of Ibero-American heads of state and heads of government 
in Cartagena de Indias, Colombia. 
  In response to a journalist's question on the Cuban leader's 
change of dress, Menem said: "It is a good omen that leads us to 
believe Cuba will soon be democratized." 
  Menem emphasized that he responded with a joke the 
journalist's question because "this style of dress suits him 
well and makes him look younger." 
  "I said it with all respect and with all my affection for 
the 
president of Cuba," said Menem, who for the first time used the 
word "president" for Castro. He previously referred to him as 
"the commander." 
  Menem later told the journalists that, during his meeting 
with U.S. President Bill Clinton, "the Cuban issue was not 
discussed." 
  Menem held informal talks with Castro in Colombia. He 
referred to the Cuban issue during a news conference at the 
Argentine Embassy in this city after meeting with Clinton at the 
White House. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

