<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Delegation's Trip to Portugal Suspended </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Delegation's Trip to Portugal Suspended </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2506030294 Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO in Portuguese 2323 GMT 
23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2506030294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the same day that the DIARIO OFICIAL carried 
authorization for a 12-member Brazilian delegation to travel to 
Lisbon, the meeting of the chiefs of state and government of 
Portuguese-speaking countries, which should have taken place in 
Lisbon tomorrow, was canceled. 
  Portuguese President Mario Soares yesterday telephoned 
President Itamar Franco to inform him that the presidents of 
Cape Verde and Angola would also not attend the meeting, and 
would send representatives instead. In view of this Mario 
Soares decided to cancel the meeting and postpone it to another 
date. The chief of the Brazilian delegation would have been 
former President Jose Sarney, and four ministers were to travel 
with him. 
  Brazilian Ambassador to Portugal Jose Aparecido de Oliveira 
did not like this cancellation, as he was one of the greatest 
enthusiasts of the meeting and of the principal point on its 
agenda: the unification of the Portuguese language. 
  Up until the very last moment Jose Aparecido tried to make 
President Itamar Franco change his mind and attend the meeting. 
When he did not convince him, Jose Aparecido became furious. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

