<F P=106> [Report by Azucena Lievano from the "24 Hours Newcast"; </F>
passages within quotation marks are recorded] 
  [Text] Minutes ago, here at the Narino Palace, 
President-elect Ernesto Samper Pizano officially announced the 
first five ministers of his cabinet. 
  [Samper] "Justice Minister Dr. Nestor Humberto Martinez." 
  He was bank superintendent, and he is currently abroad. 
  [Samper] "Government Minister Dr. Horacio Serpa Uribe." 
  He will occupy this post for a second time. He is the ideal 
person to handle the peace negotiations with the guerrillas. 
  [Samper] "Defense Minister Dr. Fernando Botero Zea." 
  He will be the second civilian to run the Defense 
Ministry--a 
big question mark for the military. 
  [Samper] "Finance Minister Dr. Guillermo Perry Rubio." 
  He has been adviser to the president-elect for many years. 
He 
has mastered public treasury matters. 
  [Samper] "Foreign Relations Minister Dr. Rodrigo Pardo." 
  He is a political expert who knows how foreign policy works. 

