A Network </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "AM/PM" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Army captured (Carlos Arturo Velandia Jagua) in 
Santa Fe de Bogota on 25 June. He is considered the fourth in 
command within the Army of National Liberation, ELN. 
  The guerrilla was at a downtown cafeteria extorting a 
citizen. Military intelligence files show that he was 
responsible for a dynamite attack on Finance Minister Rudolf 
Hommes and was involved in operations in which 56 soldiers and 
policemen died. 
  He is considered to be an expert booby trap manufacturer due 
to training he received in Vietnam. 

