<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Uruguayan Foreign Minister Arrives for Urupabol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Uruguayan Foreign Minister Arrives for Urupabol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2406181394 Asuncion Cerro Cora Sistema Nacional de 
Television Network in Spanish 1600 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2406181394 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion Cerro Cora Sistema Nacional de 
Television Network </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Uruguayan, Paraguayan, and Bolivian foreign 
ministers will relaunch Urupabol [Permanent Joint Commission of 
Uruguay, Paraguay, and Bolivia]. This organization will attempt 
to improve communications and commodity outlets through regional 
rivers and highways. 
  Uruguayan Foreign Minister Sergio Abreu Bonilla has arrived 
in Paraguay. He will participate in a ceremony to relaunch 
Urupabol, an organization made up of Uruguay, Paraguay, and 
Bolivia that was dissolved in 1982 because it was described as 
being unnecessary. 
  [Begin Abreu recording, in progress] ...a cooperation 
agreement that existed a few years ago has been revamped in the 
area, and is being implemented under Paraguay's pro tempore 
secretariat...[end recording, in progress] 
  An effort now will be made for the three countries to 
cooperate in the improvement of communications and 
transportation of commodities through the Paraguay-Parana 
waterway and the Transchaco Highway. Uruguay will offer its port 
services. 
  The Bolivian foreign minister will arrive at 1430 today. 
Urupabol will serve as a Common Market of the South, Mercosur, 
bridge for Bolivia, which is an Andean Pact member. 
  The three countries' foreign ministers will meet at 1630 
today and will sign an agreement at noon on 25 June. 
  During the Uruguayan foreign minister's visit to our 
country, 
an agreement on returning stolen motor vehicles will be signed. 
Paraguay already has signed this type of agreement with other 
South American countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

