<H3> <TI>   Revenues Under Secretary, Others Appointed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Revenues Under Secretary, Others Appointed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2506010894 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 23 Jun 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> PY2506010894 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] During the swearing-in ceremony of newly 
appointed Revenues Under Secretary Oscar Lopez Silvero, Finance 
Minister Crispiniano Sandoval said: "We need greater 
determination to combat tax evasion and smuggling. The Finance 
Ministry needs to earn the respect of society. We are collecting 
more but this is not enough. We have several commitments with 
the IMF that have yet to be accomplished." Lopez Silvero 
replaces Carlos Sosa Jovellanos, who resigned yesterday. 
  Several other replacements were announced through an 
executive branch decree. The most surprising one was that of 
Revenues Department Director Inocencio Davalos. He will be 
replaced by Castor Acosta. 
  Sandoval said the executive branch and the Finance Ministry 
are concerned about the Revenues Department performance compared 
to the progress by the Customs Directorate and the Collection 
Department (in charge of medium and small contributors). 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

