<H3> <TI>   President Rejects Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Rejects Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2406220894 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2029 GMT 24 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2406220894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 24 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- Today, President 
Carlos Salinas de Gortari rejected the resignation of Interior 
Secretary Jorge Carpizo, who had sent a letter to the president 
stating his decision to resign and retire from political life. 
  The resignation presented by Carpizo, a prestigious attorney 
and former university director, took place two months before the 
21 August elections. Nine political parties have presented 
candidates for the country's presidential elections. Carpizo 
assumed the Interior Secretariat at the beginning of the year. 

</TEXT>

