<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zedillo Reacts to Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zedillo Reacts to Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2506035694 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2506035694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Evening News Panorama" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Ernesto Zedillo Ponce de Leon, Mexican presidential 
candidate for the Institutional Revolutionary Party [PRI], has 
reacted to Interior Secretary Jorge Carpizo McGregor's letter of 
resignation. Zedillo reacted in a written statement issued 
through the National Executive Committee of his party. Zedillo 
noted that Carpizo's resignation from his post as interior 
secretary is not acceptable under any circumstance considering 
his political and moral attributes and his contribution to 
democracy, the protection of human rights, and the country's 
domestic policy of tolerance and concerted effort. There is an 
interesting paragraph in the Zedillo letter which reads: The PRI 
confirms its commitment to contributing to the efforts being 
made by Dr. Carpizo. The PRI supports Dr. Jorge Carpizo and 
cordially asks the government of the republic not to accept his 
resignation and to provide its fullest support for the work done 
by Dr. Carpizo. 
  The PRI also called on the Party of the Democratic 
Revolution 
[PRD] to immediately respond with conviction to the dialogue 
initiatives made by Carpizo in his roles as interior secretary 
and president of the General Council of the Federal Electoral 
Institute [IFE] to achieve the goals of the political forces and 
of all citizens. The PRI also asked the PRD and its supporters 
to respond to the proposals made by Dr. Carpizo at the sessions 
held at the General Council of the IFE on 18 June, in which he 
appealed for no more attitudes of confrontation. 
  It is also important to note that Ernesto Zedillo learned 
about Dr. Carpizo's letter in Toluca, Mexico State during a 
political event held with students at the technological 
institute, but the meeting was not very successful for Dr. 
Zedillo. 
  There was much emotion and joy, but that was because of the 
Mexican soccer team's victory. Dr. Zedillo said the following: 
  [Begin Zedillo recording] [Words indistinct] is for the 
national soccer team. [Students cheer] The rally has ended. Let 
us win on 21 August! [end recording] 
  When the political rally ended, Dr. Ernesto Zedillo said he 
would issue a statement on the resignation of the interior 
secretary at the PRI. He eventually did issue his statement 
through an information bulletin. At the rally, he said: Please 
let me learn more about the matter. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

