<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Carpizo Decides To Stay in Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Carpizo Decides To Stay in Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2606202194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1924 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2606202194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 26 Jun (EFE) -- Today, Jorge Carpizo 
decided to stay on as interior secretary after resigning on 24 
June. Mexican President Carlos Salinas de Gortari did not accept 
the resignation. 
  Carpizo, in a letter addressed to the president, said after 
receiving the support of broad segments of the community "and to 
prevent anyone from saying I acted irresponsibly and 
unpatriotically, I will remain in the post of interior 
secretary." 
  Carpizo's announcement averts a government crisis that many 
political analysts believe would have had serious consequences, 
if the resignation had occurred, on the political process Mexico 
is experiencing as it heads toward the 21 August presidential 
election, 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-34917 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat123_c_94010" </HT>


