<H3> <TI>   New Chiapas Peace Commissioner Meets Media </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Chiapas Peace Commissioner Meets Media </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2406172294 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2406172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report on news conference by Jorge Madrazo Cuellar, the </F>
newly appointed commissioner for peace and reconciliation in 
Chiapas, with unidentified reporters in Mexico City on 23 June; 
from the "Early Morning" newscast -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Madrazo Cuellar] I have asked the Human Rights 
Commission's Council to report on my appointment and my formal 
request to the Senate for a temporary leave of absence as 
president of the National Human Rights Commission. Once the 
Senate and the Human Rights Commission finalizes this, I will be 
ready to answer your many questions, my journalist friends. 
  I can tell you that to this important and difficult task I 
will commit all of my abilities and eagerness to legally serve 
Mexico and the president of the republic. I am asking you to be 
understanding. I hope that as soon as the legal procedures are 
completed, you and I will be able to meet in order that I can 
answer your questions. 
  [Reporter] Any conditions for resuming the talks? 
  [Madrazo Cuellar] Again, I am asking you to be understanding 
and let the procedures be completed to enable me to legally and 
respectfully answer questions from the media. 
  [Reporter] [Words indistinct] 
  [Madrazo Cuellar] Tomorrow morning. 
  [Reporter] [Words indistinct] 
  [Madrazo Cuellar] The National Commission. As soon as the 
request for the absence of leave is cleared, the office will be 
managed by Carlos Dominguez. Thank you. 

</TEXT>

