<F P=103> PA2506045394 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Cecilia Pachano; from the "Union Radio News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] Interior Minister Ramon Escovar Salom has asserted 
that the government will not allow violence to seize the 
country. He, thus, concurred with the president who said 
violence will be vigorously repressed throughout the country. 
  [Begin Escobar recording] He is bound by the Constitution 
and 
the laws of the country to guarantee public order and he is 
willing to comply with this obligation. I, as interior minister 
and as a result of my interpretation of the president's decision 
to implement this policy, am willing to take all necessary 
measures to stop violence from seizing the country. [end 
recording] 
  The interior minister also stated that national authorities 
recognize the tricks used by foreigners to illegally enter the 
country in the past. He added that the government would not 
allow such a situation to continue and he categorically stated 
that he was referring to Haitians and any other foreigners. 

