<H3> <TI>   Electoral Campaign Roundup </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electoral Campaign Roundup </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2106222594 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>
<F P=103> PY2106222594 </F>
<F P=104>  -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on developments related to the scheduled 3 October 
general elections. 
  PDT-PP Alliance in Minas Gerais -- The Minas Gerais office 
of 
the Democratic Labor Party, PDT, decided on 6 June to support 
the Popular Party, PP, candidate for the state's governorship, 
Helio Costa. In exchange Costa will allow PDT presidential 
candidate Leonel Brizola to take part in his rallies. According 
to Brizola, this alliance "will open up new possibilities not 
only in Minas Gerais, but also in the rest of Brazil." It has 
also been decided that Senator Darcy Ribeiro, vice presidential 
candidate on Brizola's ticket, will concentrate his electoral 
campaign in Sao Paulo, Minas Gerais, and Rio de Janeiro. (Rio 
de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 7 Jun 94 p 6) 
  Paraiba PMDB Not To Support Lula -- The decision of the PT 
gubernatorial candidate in Paraiba State, Avenzoar Arruda, not 
to give up his candidacy has caused former Paraiba Governor 
Ronaldo Cunha Lima, who is the local Brazilian Democratic 
Movement Party leader and Senate candidate on Antonio Mariz' 
ticket, to withdraw his support for the presidential candidacy 
of the PT's Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva. (Rio de Janeiro JORNAL 
DO BRASIL in Portuguese 12 Jun 94 p 2) 

</TEXT>

