  [Text] Ankara, 21 Jun (PL) -- It was reported today that 
Turkey and Cuba have assessed the possibility of increasing 
economic ties, especially in the areas of commerce, tourism, and 
business. 
  Those possibilities were studied during Cuban Ambassador to 
Turkey Jorge Castro's visit to the city of Izmir, an important 
agricultural and industrial center in Turkey, where he met with 
local authorities and industrial and commercial representatives. 
  The report given by Cuba's diplomatic office added that they 
had agreed to hold a meeting of Turkish and Cuban businessmen 
shortly to determine Cuba's participation in the construction of 
houses in that city. 
  Jorge Castro's two-day visit allowed him to discuss, in a 
friendly atmosphere, the development of bilateral economic ties 
and tourism investment and to give Izmir Mayor Burhan Dapatura a 
message from his Cuban counterpart, Pedro Chavez. 

