<H3> <TI>   Two More Leave Belgian Ambassador's Residence </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two More Leave Belgian Ambassador's Residence </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2706210394 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1941 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2706210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 27 Jun (EFE) -- Today, official sources 
reported that on Sunday [26 June], two Cuban citizens left the 
Belgian ambassador's residence in Havana. Sixty-nine of a total 
of 124 persons who jumped over the fence of the residence to 
obtain political asylum on 28 May remain at the diplomatic 
mission. 
  Since then, a total of 55 persons, among them several women 
and children, have left the diplomatic mission, accepting the 
guarantees offered by the Cuban authorities that they will not 
be subject to legal proceedings for entering the embassy. 
  A week ago, the Cuban Government announced it will not 
authorize the departure from the country of any Cuban who 
forcibly enters a diplomatic mission. A total of 21 persons 
remain at the German Embassy in Havana, while the eight 
occupants of the Chilean Consulate General left the mission last 
week. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

