<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Evening Information Review" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Fernando Remirez de Estenoz, Cuban ambassador to the 
United Nations, has said his country applauds the Group of 77's 
resolve to continue contributing to strengthening the role of 
the highest international organization in promoting economic 
growth and development. Speaking to the ministerial level 
meeting on the 30th anniversary of the aforementioned group, the 
Cuban diplomat said the premises and principles that brought 
about the creation of that movement continue to be as valid and 
necessary as before. 

