<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Prices for Gasoline To Be Implemented 1 Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Prices for Gasoline To Be Implemented 1 Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2706214894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2706214894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Radio News"] </F>
  [Text] As of 1 July, the Ministry of Prices and Finance, 
through the 23 June Resolution No. 8, will establish new prices 
for fuels that are sold for personal use through fuel ration 
cards. The prices, agreed upon by the executive committee of the 
Council of Ministers are: 1.20 pesos per liter for special 
gasoline; 1 peso per liter for regular gasoline; 75 cents per 
liter of gas oil or diesel. 
  The resolution establishes that the money will be collected 
when the private-use fuel ration cards are issued to consumers 
in the places designated by the enterprises that are authorized 
to operate the service centers. The fuel ration cards will be 
given out, in the same manner as before, according to Cuba's 
fuel supply. 
  The enterprises that will supply and charge for the fuel 
ration cards for private use will guarantee that they have no 
expiration date and that those not used by year end, for any 
reason, can be renewed during the period that the said 
enterprises establish. A private vehicle owner who has a 1994 
fuel ration card when the new prices become effective can renew 
them before 31 July 1994 in the same place where he got them. He 
will have to pay the difference between the old and new prices. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

