<H3> <TI>   Salinas `Pleased' With Carpizo's Decision To Remain </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salinas `Pleased' With Carpizo's Decision To Remain </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2706144194 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2706144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Carlos Salinas has said he is very pleased 
with Dr. Jorge Carpizo's decision to continue as interior 
secretary and president of the Federal Electoral Institute. The 
president also expressed his satisfaction with the people's 
support for Dr. Carpizo, support which demonstrates, he has 
said, the broad resolve to progress with democracy in accordance 
with the law and without violence. Salinas has also reiterated 
his total support for Dr. Carpizo to continue leading the 
electoral process in the next few months. 
  Salinas said the recent public expressions of support for 
Dr. 
Carpizo's independent, party, and honest attitude reaffirm the 
conviction the country will meet the task of holding clean and 
impartial elections in accordance with the law and with respect 
for the country's political pluralism. 

</TEXT>

