  [Text] Bonivert Claude, governor of the Central Bank of 
Haiti, denied the allegation that General Raoul Cedras withdrew 
$500,000. THE WASHINGTON POST had asserted that the head of the 
Haitian Army, Gen. Cedras, had withdrawn $500,000 from whatever 
strong currency remains in the Haitian central bank. Quoting 
government officials and members of Haitian banking circles, the 
newspaper explained that the reasons for this withdrawal were 
not clear. Claude exclaims: This is impossible! The general does 
not have an account at the Central Bank. Claude further pointed 
out that the bank is concerned with the currency problem 
affecting the Haitian financial system, and looks for a quick 
solution to this problem. 

