<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Departs for New York </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Departs for New York </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2706164294 Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 26 Jun 94 p 19 </F>
<F P=103> PY2706164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ABC COLOR </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 25 June, Paraguayan Foreign Minister Dr. Luis 
Maria Ramirez Boettner traveled to New York (United States) 
where he will participate in a meeting sponsored by Ecosoc 
[Economic and Social Council], a UN economic and social 
organization. The meetings will begin on 27 June and end on 29 
June. 
  Paraguay joined Ecosoc last year and this is the first time 
a 
Paraguayan foreign minister will participate in these meetings. 
  The Paraguayan foreign minister will travel from New York to 
London to join a presidential entourage that will begin an 
official visit to the UK that will end on 7 July [date as 
published]. 
<H5>  Bolivian and Uruguayan Foreign Ministers Depart </H5>
  Bolivian Foreign Minister Antonio Aranibar Quiroga and 
Uruguayan Foreign Minister Sergio Abreu Bonilla returned to 
their respective countries on 25 June after participating in 
meetings in Asuncion to relaunch Urupabol [Permanent Joint 
Commission of Uruguay, Paraguay, and Bolivia], a political 
organization that was dissolved in 1982 because it was described 
as being unnecessary. 

</TEXT>

