<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Menem Reaffirms No Intervention in Haiti </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Menem Reaffirms No Intervention in Haiti </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2706173594 Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network in Spanish 
1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2706173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Carlos Menem emphasized today that 
Argentina will not participate in a probable military 
intervention in Haiti outside UN resolutions. 
  The Argentine president guaranteed that the government will 
ask Congress for authorization if the United Nations makes a 
decision for our country to send military forces to that 
Caribbean island where a coup overthrew a democratic president 
in 1991. 
  President Carlos Menem also urged the United States to 
increase political and economic measures against Haiti's de 
facto government in order to restore the democratic system in 
that country. 

</TEXT>

