<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Frei Departs for Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Frei Departs for Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2706142394 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1100 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2706142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Eduardo Frei departed for a three-day 
visit to the United States at 2045 on 26 June. During his brief 
trip to the United States, Frei is scheduled to hold meetings 
with top-ranking U.S. political and economic officials, the most 
important of which will be his meeting with U.S. President Bill 
Clinton. It is expected that the two presidents will surely 
discuss the Chilean-U.S. free trade agreement during this 
meeting. 
  Before his departure, the president headed the traditional 
transfer-of-power ceremony. During this ceremony, President 
Eduardo Frei transferred the presidency to Interior Minister 
German Correa in compliance with a decree read previously by 
Interior Under Secretary Belisario Velasco. German Correa 
assumed the presidency in his capacity as Chilean vice president. 
  Before boarding the plane that would take him to the United 
States, President Frei stated that his meeting with Bill Clinton 
does not seek solely commercial objectives: 
  [Begin Frei recording] This visit has much broader 
objectives. The free trade treaty is, of course, among the 
issues that will be discussed. This is not, however, the only 
issue to be discussed. There are many other issues. We are most 
interested in strengthening our political ties, on having fluent 
bilateral ties with the United States in vast areas. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

