<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Citizens Back Frei Administration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Shows Citizens Back Frei Administration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2706213694 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1800 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2706213694 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Most Chileans support President Eduardo Frei's 
administration even though this support is less than President 
Aylwin received during his first 90 days of government. 
  According to an Adimark poll conducted in Greater Santiago, 
54 percent support President Frei's administration, 15 percent 
disapprove, while 31 percent neither approves nor disapproves. 
Comparing these figures with the first 90 days of former 
President Aylwin's government, the support level is lower. 
  Concerning pending matters, 41 percent believe the 
government 
badly handled the case of [Carabineros Director General] Rodolfo 
Stange, 36 percent believe it handled it well, and 22 percent 
said they do not know. 
  Most Chileans believe Gen. Stange should resign. 

</TEXT>

