<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Rebels' Attack Military Outpost at Camp Perin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2806221394 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 
GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2806221394 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Some rebel activity has been reported in the 
southern region and in Grand-Anse by the Haitian Army's 
headquarters. A group of armed men attacked a military outpost 
atm Camp Perin during the night of 19 June, according to Army 
headquarters. According to a high-ranking officer of the Haitian 
Army, one rebel was killed and the Army sustained one injury. 
The soldier on duty in the Camp Perin subdistrict reportedly 
received a bullet wound in the leg during an exchange of shots 
with the rebels who, it is reported, numbered around 20. 
According to this high-ranking officer of the Haitian Army, 
following the exchanges, the group spread out to the south and 
in Grand-Anse, where they are being pursued by military units. 
In Grand-Anse, a peasant was reported killed by one of the 
rebels who later took his own life. [words indistinct] 

</TEXT>

