<F P=100> CENTRAL AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Costa Rica </F>
<H3> <TI>   Colombian Drug Suspect To Be Extradited to U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Colombian Drug Suspect To Be Extradited to U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2906003194 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 2034 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2906003194 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] San Jose, 28 Jun (ACAN-EFE) -- The Costa Rican 
police today reported that a Colombian citizen, a top money 
laundering suspect sought by U.S. authorities, was arrested in 
Costa Rica as he arrived from Colombia. 
  The Judicial Investigations Agency (OIJ) reported that Juan 
Crisostomo Trujillo Martinez was arrested on 24 June after he 
arrived in Costa Rica aboard a flight from Santa Fe de Bogota. 
Trujillo's arrest took place after U.S. Customs alerted the OIJ 
to the pending arrival of the Colombian, whom the United States 
has linked to the "laundering" of large amounts of Cali Cartel 
money. 
  According to sources, Trujillo did not have contacts in 
Costa 
Rica. Rather, he arrived here after U.S. authorities set him up 
to travel to this Central American nation. The suspect, who 
remains in custody at a jail in San Jose, will be extradited to 
the United States within the next few days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

