<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2806150394 </F>
<F P=103> PA2806150394 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Honduran economic developments monitored through 28 
June. 
  Authorities of the Central Bank of Honduras, BCH, decided 
yesterday to hold daily dollar auctions beginning 23 June. Bank 
spokesman Juan Soto said the auction will operate much like a 
stock market. (San Pedro Sula EL TIEMPO in Spanish 22 June 94 p 
2) 
  An official source reported today the BCH sold $2.9 million 
during its first U.S. currency auction. The post-auction 
exchange rate was 8.67 lempiras per dollar. These auctions are 
among the measures recently adopted by Honduran banking 
authorities to stop the increasing devaluation of the local 
currency. Local bank figures indicate the lempira suffered a 
devaluation of at least 13 percent during the first five months 
of 1994. (Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1800 GMT 24 June 94) 

</TEXT>

