<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ex-Recontras Enter Colombian Embassy, Demand Asylum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ex-Recontras Enter Colombian Embassy, Demand Asylum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2806192294 Paris AFP in Spanish 1807 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2806192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Managua, 28 Jun (AFP) -- Seven former Nicaraguan 
recontras (rearmed contras) entered the Colombian Embassy in 
this capital today to demand political asylum, Government 
Ministry sources reported. 
  Another group of 15 former recontras of the so-called 3-80 
Northern Front, an armed group which demobilized in April, 
occupied the offices of the OAS International Commission of 
Support and Verification (CIAV-OAS) in a simultaneous act this 
morning, demanding government compliance with the disarmament 
agreements, official sources confirmed. 
  Although the former rebels inside the Colombian Embassy have 
not publicized the reasons for demanding asylum, local sources 
believe both actions seek the same objective: to exert pressure 
demanding compliance with the agreements in which the government 
offered them protection, land, and the participation of a former 
guerrilla sector in the police, among other things. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

