<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Endara Appoints New Education Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Endara Appoints New Education Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2806172394 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2806172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "RPC Television News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Presidency Information and Public Relations 
Office of the Republic has released a communique announcing that 
by executive decree signed by President Guillermo Endara 
Galimany, educator German Vergara has been appointed education 
minister. Professor Vergara has been appointed due to the 
retirement of current Education Minister Marcos Alarcon, 
effective 1 July. The communique adds Professor Vergara is the 
current Health Ministry secretary general. 
  The executive decree will become effective on 1 July. RPC 
tried to obtain reactions from Education Minister Alarcon as 
well as from Professor Vergara, but both declined to comment. 
The two men are members of the Arnulfist Party. 
  Meanwhile, teachers union leaders have expressed hope the 
new 
appointment will foster a better understanding between teachers 
and the Education Ministry. Efrain de Leon, of the Association 
of Independent Teachers, has commented on the issue: 
  [Begin de Leon recording] He represents the executive 
branch; 
therefore, he represents a political party and will function 
with political guidelines. We also know that working against 
him is his term of almost two months. We hope he will try 
during this period to correct the many mistakes Alarcon has made 
and reach an agreement, for the first time during this period of 
democracy, between the Education Ministry and the teachers 
unions. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

