<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   CNEA Head Denies Construction of Nuclear Plant </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CNEA Head Denies Construction of Nuclear Plant </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2806200594 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1250 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2806200594 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cordoba, 28 Jun (NA) -- Manuel Mondino, the National 
Commission for Atomic Energy [CNEA] chairman, has denied that 
the construction of a new nuclear power plant in Cordoba is 
being reconsidered and holds journalists responsible for 
disseminating inaccurate reports on this issue. 
  The CNEA chairman categorically stressed that "no decision 
has been made." He added that "a decision may be made by the 
end of the year, if it is made at all." 
  Mondino was very angry with journalists. He stressed that 
neither "the National Government, the CNEA, nor anyone else has 
ever discussed the construction of a second nuclear power plant." 
  Mondino described as "nonsense" reports released during 
President Carlos Menem's visit to Canada, where Menem addressed 
the issue. 

</TEXT>

