<H3> <TI>   Further on Alleged Drug-Funding of Campaign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Alleged Drug-Funding of Campaign </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    New `Narcocassette' Disclosed </H4>

<F P=102> PA2806192194 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2806192194 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by J.J. Pinilla from the "National Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] A new narcocassette was just disclosed, and those 
who sent it assured have us that it contains new evidence on the 
involvement of drug funds in the political campaigns. Here is a 
report by J.J. Pinilla: 
  [Begin Pinilla recording] Attention. A communique and a 
cassette have just been dropped off at the "National Newscast" 
reception desk. In this cassette, a group called Honorable 
Colombians reveals two messages: The first message includes 
statements by journalist Alberto Giraldo and Gilberto Rodriguez 
Orejuela; it deals with a meeting between Giraldo and Santiago 
Medina, Samper's campaign treasurer. In this meeting Gilberto 
Rodriguez Orejuela confirms that the Cali Cartel funded Samper's 
campaign. The second message contains statements by Alberto 
Giraldo and Miguel Rodriguez Orejuela. The topic revolves 
around the, quote, honorable, unquote, General Miguel Maza 
Marquez's receiving money from the Cali Cartel. 
  The communique was also sent to the Supreme Court of 
Justice, 
the Prosecutor General's Office, the Attorney General's Office, 
all the media, and the French and U.S. Embassies. The "National 
Newscast" has not yet disclosed the contents of the cassette 
because the voices of the people in it have not been identified. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

