<H3> <TI>   Further on Alleged Drug-Funding of Campaign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Alleged Drug-Funding of Campaign </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Cali Cartel Chief Denies Contribution </H4>

<F P=102> PA2906015094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2258 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2906015094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Santa Fe de Bogota, 28 Jun (EFE) -- According to 
SEMANA magazine, Gilberto Rodriguez Orejuela, the paramount 
leader of the "Cali Cartel," telephoned a subdirector of EL 
TIEMPO daily to swear to him on lives of his children that he 
did not make any contributions to any of the presidential 
candidates. 
  The magazine assures that last Thursday [23 June] "amid the 
scandal caused by the alleged injection of hot money into the 
electoral contest," Rodrigo Orejuela called reporter Enrique 
Santos Castillo to explicitly tell him that his organization did 
not make any contributions to any of the candidates. 
  The scandal, which resulted from the disclosure of 
audiocassette recordings of conversations between reporter 
Alberto Giraldo and the brothers Gilberto and Miguel Rodriguez 
Orejuela, has tainted Liberal candidate Ernesto Samper's 19 June 
election victory. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

