<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Legislators Visit ROK, Support Nonproliferation Treaties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Legislators Visit ROK, Support Nonproliferation Treaties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2806151394 Lima EL PERUANO in Spanish 22 Jun 94 p A1 </F>
<F P=103> PY2806151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima EL PERUANO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul -- The delegation of Peruvian legislators 
visiting Seoul in response to an invitation extended by the ROK 
National Assembly have expressed the need for strict adherence 
to nuclear nonproliferation treaties, which they said are the 
only guarantees for peaceful coexistence. 
  The delegation of Peruvian legislators comprising Oswaldo 
Sandoval Aguirre, Carlos Blanco Oropeza, and Antero Flores Araoz 
warned that the nuclear subject is an issue that concerns the 
entire world and not only the Korean peninsula. The Peruvian 
legislators also expressed their hope that mechanisms of 
understandings will be achieved to avoid any armed conflicts. 
  After meeting ROK Parliamentary speaker Yi Man-sop, the 
Peruvian legislators said: We hope the right of South Koreans to 
live in peace will be respected. "Our countries want peace not 
war because only thus we will be able to achieve our countries' 
development." 

</TEXT>

