<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Increased Trade With Colombia Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Increased Trade With Colombia Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2806151094 </F>
<F P=103> PA2806151094 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial report] Hamburg DPA in Spanish at 1815 GMT on 21 
June reports the official news agency VENPRES reported today 
Venezuelan-Colombian trade grew by 128 percent in 1993 compared 
to 1992. It added Colombia is the main market for Venezuelan 
nonpetroleum exports, which totaled approximately $1.6 billion 
in 1993. 

