<H3> <TI>   Former President Not To Run in 1995 Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former President Not To Run in 1995 Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2706203594 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2706203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Former Peruvian President Fernando Belaunde Terry 
has confirmed that he will not run for president in 1995. He 
said he would be an active participant in the presidential 
campaign, but not a presidential candidate. The Popular Action, 
AP, leader said that he does not believe in polls, and added 
that his party plans to participate in the presidential 
elections with its own presidential candidate. 
  Belaunde Terry said that AP does not need to improve any 
policy, but rather project a path into the future. 

</TEXT>

