<F P=106> [Report by Luiz Augusto Mendonca in Brasilia] </F>
  [Text] The minimum wage will be $70 on 1 September. 
President Itamar Franco made this decision following a meeting 
with the finance, labor, and social security ministers, and the 
federal administration secretary. 
  Labor Minister Marcelo Pimentel later said that by the end 
of 
October the government will send Congress a draft bill outlining 
a new minimum wage policy. President Itamar said military and 
public servants will receive a salary adjustment soon after the 
implementation of the real. The president said the date for the 
wage increase has yet to be established, but it will be 
implemented even if he has to fight with his economic ministers. 

