<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister Explains Measures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Minister Explains Measures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2906021394 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2906021394 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Annerys Gonzalez; from "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Regarding the suspension of constitutional 
guarantees, Interior Minister Ramon Escovar Salom explained that 
the right to stage peaceful demonstrations has not been 
suspended. 
  [Begin Escovar recording] I have told people that the fact 
that the guarantees have been suspended does not mean that the 
government is going to become a dictatorship, nor does it mean 
that the government is going to suppress the rights of citizens. 
I have asked them to expect a prudent attitude, a discreet, but 
at the same time stern attitude on the part of the government. 
[end recording] 
  The interior minister will meet in his office today with the 
governor of the federal district and the chiefs of the various 
security corps of the state to discuss the security situation in 
the country. The objective of the meeting is to define the 
security strategies to be followed during the time that certain 
constitutional guarantees are suspended. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

