<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Matanzas Central Army Military Units Inspected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Matanzas Central Army Military Units Inspected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2906151894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2906151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Doing Radio" program] </F>
  [Text] Military units in Matanzas Province are undergoing 
an inspection aimed at reviewing the progress of the fulfillment 
of the Central Army and Revolutionary Armed Forces strategic 
guidelines. The Central Army inspection will conclude on 1 July. 
It includes the provincial General Staff and Matanzas and Union 
de Reyes Municipalities, as well as the Camilo Cienfuegos and 
Comandante Horacio Schools. 
  The inspection of the provincial defense system will also 
review the Revolutionary Navy's efforts, as well as the progress 
of efforts to achieve second phase status in defense 
preparedness. The combat training of the Territorial Troops 
Militia, special units, and Production and Defense Brigades in 
the province will also be evaluated. 
  On 28 June at 2000, the Camilo Cienfuegos Military School 
held the first provincial defense system amateur artists 
festival. The most culturally active municipality of the Central 
Army will be selected tonight. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
